seg.name: Patient Adverse Reaction Information
seg.desc: The IAM segment contains person/patient adverse reaction information of various types.

seg.name: Financial Transaction
seg.desc: The FT1 segment contains the detail data necessary to post charges, payments, adjustments, etc. to patient accounting records.

seg.name: Event Type
seg.desc: The EVN segment is used to communicate necessary trigger event information to receiving applications.

seg.name: Appointment Information - Location Resource 1
seg.desc: The AIL segment contains information about location resources (meeting rooms, operating rooms, examination rooms, or other locations) that can be scheduled.

seg.name: Override Segment
seg.desc: This segment allows a sender to override specific receiving application’s business rules to allow for processing of a message that would normally be rejected or ignored.

seg.name: Timing / Quantity
seg.desc: The TQ1 segment is used to specify the complex timing of events and actions such as those that occur in order management and scheduling systems.

seg.name: Observations that are Calculated from Other Observations
Merge Patient Information
seg.desc: The MRG segment provides receiving applications with information necessary to initiate the merging of patient data as well as groups of records.

seg.name: Patient Allergy Information
seg.desc: The AL1 segment contains patient allergy information of various types.

seg.name: Guarantor
seg.desc: The GT1 segment contains guarantor (e.g., the person or the organization with financial responsibility for payment of a patient account) data for patient and insurance billing applications.

seg.name: UB82
seg.desc: The UB1 segment contains the data necessary to complete UB82 bills specific to the United States; other realms may choose to implement using regional code sets.

seg.name: Risk Management Incident
seg.desc: The RMI segment is used to report an occurrence of an incident event pertaining or attaching to a patient encounter.

seg.name: Master File Acknowledgment
seg.desc: The Technical Steward for the MFA segment is CQ.

seg.name: Appointment Information - General Resource 1
seg.desc: The AIG segment contains information about various kinds of resources (other than those with specifically defined segments in this chapter) that can be scheduled.

seg.name: Display Data
seg.desc: The DSP segment is used to contain data that has been preformatted by the sender for display.

seg.name: Appointment Request 1
seg.desc: The ARQ segment defines a request for the booking of an appointment.

seg.name: File Header
seg.desc: The FHS segment is used to head a file (group of batches)

seg.name: Insurance Additional Information
seg.desc: The IN2 segment contains additional insurance policy coverage and benefit information necessary for proper billing and reimbursement.

seg.name: Message Header
seg.desc: The MSH segment defines the intent, source, destination, and some specifics of the syntax of a message.

seg.name: Observation / Result
seg.desc: The OBX segment is used to transmit a single observation or observation fragment.

seg.name: Error
seg.desc: The ERR segment is used to add error comments to acknowledgment messages.

seg.name: Resource Group 1
seg.desc: The RGS segment is used to identify relationships between resources identified for a scheduled event.

seg.name: Next of Kin / Associated Parties
seg.desc: The NK1 segment contains information about the patient’s other related parties.

seg.name: Batch Header
seg.desc: The BHS segment defines the start of a batch.

seg.name: Common Order
seg.desc: The Common Order segment (ORC) is used to transmit fields that are common to all orders (all types of services that are requested).

seg.name: Imaging Procedure Control Segment
seg.desc: The IPC segment contains information about tasks that need to be performed in order to fulfill the request for imaging service.

seg.name: File Trailer
seg.desc: The FTS segment defines the end of a file.

seg.name: Appointment Information - Personnel Resource 1
seg.desc: The AIP segment contains information about the personnel types that can be scheduled.

seg.name: Blood Code
seg.desc: The BLC segment contains data necessary to communicate patient abstract blood information used for billing and reimbursement purposes.

seg.name: Accident
seg.desc: The ACC segment contains patient information relative to an accident in which the patient has been involved.

seg.name: Patient Additional Demographic
seg.desc: The patient additional demographic segment contains demographic information that is likely to change about the patient.

seg.name: Insurance Additional Information, Certification
seg.desc: The IN3 segment contains additional insurance information for certifying the need for patient care.

seg.name: Procedures
seg.desc: The PR1 segment contains information relative to various types of procedures that can be performed on a patient.

seg.name: Master File Entry
seg.desc: The Technical Steward for the MFE segment is CQ.

seg.name: Continuation Pointer
seg.desc: The DSC segment is used in the continuation protocol.

seg.name: Insurance
seg.desc: The IN1 segment contains insurance policy coverage information necessary to produce properly pro-rated and patient and insurance bills.

seg.name: UB92 Data
seg.desc: The UB2 segment contains data necessary to complete UB92 bills specific to the United States; other realms may choose to implement using regional code sets.

seg.name: Addendum
seg.desc: The ADD segment is used to define the continuation of the prior segment in a continuation message.

seg.name: Patient Identification
seg.desc: The PID segment is used by all applications as the primary means of communicating patient identification information. This segment contains permanent patient identifying and demographic information that, for the most part, is not likely to change frequently.

seg.name: Patient Visit
seg.desc: The PV1 segment is used by Registration/Patient Administration applications to communicate information on an account or visit-specific basis.

seg.name: Appointment Information 1
seg.desc: The AIS segment contains information about various kinds of services that can be scheduled.

seg.name: Patient Death and Autopsy
seg.desc: This segment carries information on a patient’s death and possible autopsy.

seg.name: Timing / Quantity Relationship
seg.desc: The TQ2 segment is used to form a relationship between the service request the TQ1/TQ2 segments are associated with, and other service requests.

seg.name: Observation Request
seg.desc: The Observation Request (OBR) segment is used to transmit information specific to an order for a diagnostic study or observation, physical exam, or assessment.

seg.name: Patient Visit - Additional Information
seg.desc: The PV2 segment is a continuation of information contained on the PV1 segment.

seg.name: Abstract
seg.desc: This segment was created to communicate patient abstract information used for billing and reimbursement purposes.

seg.name: Master File Identification
seg.desc: The Technical Steward for the MFI segment is CQ.

seg.name: Diagnosis Related Group
seg.desc: The DRG segment contains diagnoses-related grouping information of various types.

seg.name: Transcription Document Header
seg.desc: The TXA segment contains information specific to a transcribed document but does not include the text of the document.

seg.name: Scheduling Activity Information 1
seg.desc: The SCH segment contains general information about the scheduled appointment.

seg.name: Billing
seg.desc: The BLG segment is used to provide billing information, on the ordered service, to the filling application.

seg.name: Grouping / Reimbursement - Procedure Line Item
seg.desc: This segment is used for items that pertain to each HCPC/CPT line item.

seg.name: Bed Status Update
seg.desc: The NPU segment allows the updating of census (bed status) data without sending patient-specific data.

seg.name: Grouping / Reimbursement - Visit
seg.desc: These fields are used in grouping and reimbursement for CMS APCs.

seg.name: Diagnosis
seg.desc: The DG1 segment contains patient diagnosis information of various types, for example, admitting, primary, etc.

seg.name: Software Segment
seg.desc: This segment provides additional information about the software product(s) used as a Sending Application.

seg.name: Disability
seg.desc: The disability segment contains information related to the disability of a person.

seg.name: Specimen
seg.desc: The intent of this segment is to describe the characteristics of a specimen.

seg.name: Message Acknowledgment
seg.desc: The MSA segment contains information sent while acknowledging another message.

seg.name: Appointment Preferences 1
seg.desc: The APR segment contains parameters and preference specifications used for requesting appointments in the SRM message.

seg.name: Blood Product Transfusion / Disposition
seg.desc: The BTS segment defines the end of a batch.
